          "description": "I went to city MD East 23rd to see if doctors who had previously seen me could recommend physical therapy closer to home and not only this time but every other time it has been so efficient. Everybody is so nice. They\u2019re also personable witches really difficult to find in healthcare. They were unbiased. It was a lovely multicultural atmosphere. I\u2019ve never felt more at home. Truly, these people are so good. I wish they were a regular clinic, but they are only urgent care. I\u2019ve worked an urgent care before and let me tell you it can be chaotic and this is the opposite of chaotic. It is soothing and has great function and flow.",
